Background



		Received his bachelors degree in Mathematics from the University of Minnesota

		Prior to Forming Radian, Chris spent several years in Major CPG & Supply Chain Management firms




Highlights



		Over 25 years Food and CPG experience across many process domains including marketing, planning, strategy development, supply chain management, and logistics.

		Developed innovative methodologies, processes and technologies that drive real value and transform how category planning is implemented within retailers and suppliers.

		Led numerous engagements with Fresh foods – both within retailers organization and commodity suppliers -- and developed complex profitability measurement and decision support technologies.




