CareerCenter
Achievement is one thing; fulfillment is another.
Now hiring intellectual horsepower. 


 

Why Radian

The Ideal Candidate

Our Roles

Positions





	Radian is comprised of intelligent individuals who enjoy collaborating to enable meaningful change for our clients. Our services span multiple industries and business processes, with a specialization in Retail and Trade Partner Business Planning and Retail Event Management.

	Our associates were drawn to Radian for the opportunity to be part of a growing company and to see their work have tangible, lasting impact. We hire talented individuals who have a strong desire to be in the driver’s seat when it comes to all aspects of their careers: their development, their advancement, and their work-life balance. They prefer a nimble and straightforward working environment where the path is made clear for them to do great work. Think you might be a good fit? Learn more about the Ideal Candidate.

Our Working Philosophy


		We do great work.
	



	This simple, four-word statement actually says a lot about us. We operate as a team. We deliver for our clients, day in and day out. What we deliver is high quality and is the result of our intense efforts to achieve a goal. When it comes down to it, Radian is about smart individuals working together and collaborating on meaningful change for our clients.




		Achievement is one thing; fulfillment is another.
	



	Though we are definitely the type to set goals and achieve them, we are really interested in taking on the right challenges. We take the time to be sure we are tackling the most important and substantial problems for our clients. The work you will do at Radian will be fulfilling because it will always yield real, positive business results.




		We hire action-minded people.
	



	We hire people that are capable of not only identifying the process and business gaps, but of building the bridges to traverse them. We seek analytical and creative minds that enjoy connecting data points to form a clear picture of what is and what could be.




		We hire motivated people.
	



	The Radian leadership team sees its role as making the path clear to allow you to do the best work possible and to learn as much as you want. For the self-starter, it is like becoming an entrepreneur—with a lot more support.




		Your growth is in your hands.
	



	Your personal and professional growth with Radian will be driven by positive interactions with your team, leadership, and clients—ones that will deepen your skills and broaden your knowledge. We swap one-size-fits-all development plans for those that are customized and experiential, as these are often the best teachers and yield the greatest success.




		We still know how to relax.
	



	We expect flexibility, and we give it in return. There is no invisible time clock here, no prize for being first in and last out. Associates are expected to meet their deadlines and support their clients and team members but are also encouraged to have a fulfilling and interesting life.


 

Benefits
We at Radian believe in finding and keeping the best talent, and so our compensation packages are highly competitive. We also believe our employees should support and balance their career ambitions with a healthy lifestyle. A healthy, fulfilling personal life will only add to productivity in the workplace, so we augment our compensation with generous health and wellness benefits. Below is a summary of the benefits offered to Radian employees:


		Savings & Retirement
	





401(k) Plan

			Employees are eligible to contribute to a 401(k) account after a three-month waiting period. Radian offers a matching contribution of 25% for each dollar an eligible employee contributes, up to 8 percent of the eligible compensation.






		Lifestyle
	





Paid Time Off

			Paid-time off (PTO) days are flexible days that an employee can use for vacation, sick leave, and personal time. The number of paid-time off days is based on the employee’s career level, ranging from 10-15 days a year.



Holidays

			The annual calendar at Radian includes 8 paid holidays for employees with 2 floating holidays. 



Flexible Work

			Employees at Radian are encouraged to manage their personal priorities along with their professional commitments. Though the needs of our clients dictate some aspects of the workweek, Radian is committed to help employees strike a balance. The leadership team works hard to limit travel to only what is really required, with most of it occurring in the middle of the week. Beyond that, we trust our employees to get their work done without having to micro-manage their time.



Relaxed Environment

			Team days at the start and close of each week allow Radian team members to connect in a collegial, engaging environment. Group lunches, casual dress codes, and an overall relaxed setting help employees to recharge for what’s ahead.






		Health
	





			Radian covers a majority of the employee premium for a Preferred Provider Organization (PPO), along with a portion of the dependent coverage premium.* Radian also offers a Health Savings Account (HSA) for health-related expenses for the employee and his/her family; investment options and pre-tax contributions for the HSA are also available.



			Radian covers the employee premium, along with a portion of the dependent coverage premium.*



Radian covers the employee premium for a life-insurance policy.*



Radian offers long-term disability benefits, which are payable to eligible individuals after 90 days. Radian covers the employee premium for this insurance.


*Eligible first of month after date of hire




 





	Is Radian the Right Fit For You?

	We hire talented individuals who have a strong desire to be in the driver’s seat when it comes to their careers. They prefer a nimble and straightforward working environment where the path is clear for them to have an impact. The specific skills and background of our employees vary—and we view that diversity as a strength—but all of our employees share these common characteristics.

Natural Leaders:
	Understand how to influence decisions and drive toward resolution, regardless of their role or experience level.

Analytical Problem Solvers:
	Enjoy generating ideas, but are equally committed to seeing them through, designing and implementing plans that transform those ideas into tangible results.

Entrepreneurial:
	Thrive in entrepreneurial environments; enjoy wearing many hats, do whatever is necessary, and have unwavering tenacity.

Collaborators:
	Balance being independent thinkers with knowing how to work as part of a team; share their experience and willingly spend time helping other team members develop their skills.  

Resilient:
	Adaptable to many environments and have the flexibility and courage to change course when the situation requires it.

Motivated:
	Self-starting individuals that welcome a good challenge. See doing great work as a reward in and of itself.

	 

