James Jackson
Director










James Jackson
Director





	Why did you choose Radian?

	I chose to work at Radian because I had a dream of doing consulting, helping other people. I had grown tired of delivering information with a bias towards selling product. I wanted to have an impact on business.

	What do you most enjoy about what you do?

	I enjoy finding the needle in the haystack and connecting the dots. I love presenting: capturing the room and getting others to a level of understanding.

	What are your passions outside of work?

	I love my family: my wife of 21 years, Regina, and my three daughters, Renae, Jasmine, and Julia. I am a sports fanatic so I will usually turn the conversation with something like, "Did you see the game last night?" or, "Who are your top five power forwards, all-time?” Putting it all together, I enjoy sitting with my wife watching my kids play a slew of sports except basketball, my first true love.

	What advice would you give new hires?

	Go beyond for the benefit of your client - make life easier for them and they will trust you. Challenge yourself to find areas where we can improve and innovate - think about what the client needs. You don't add value unless something gets implemented - fancy presentations and analytics without action is dead. 

	What has been your favorite moment at Radian?

	It is hard to pinpoint one moment. It's really been about the journey: my growth as a businessperson and my approach to the challenges that I face.

	 

	To learn more about Radian email me at JJackson@radiangroup.com

	 








