Ambuj Agarwal
Senior Analyst










Ambuj Agarwal
Senior Analyst





	Why did you choose Radian?

	Choosing Radian was a much easier decision than I thought. I came to know about Radian through Roger, who is a Longhorn, and we entered into conversation about possibilities. When I interviewed with Radian, I got a chance to meet the people and that removed any doubts in my mind. I was looking for a dynamic, independent and a fun work environment where everyone works with each other. I got exactly that at Radian.

	What do you most enjoy about what you do?

	The thing I enjoy the most is the freedom I have been given at the work place. I am in charge of my own workload and I pace it as fast as I can manage. With the exceptional variety in projects available, I am sometimes spoiled for choice and that keeps me motivated.

	What are your passions outside of work?

	Fortunately (or unfortunately) I am not passionate about any thing in particular outside of work. I like to try a lot of different things and that leaves me doing something new every weekend. When I did not know Nashville, I thought it was boring; now I can hardly stop talking about Nashville.

	What advice would you give new hires?

	At Radian, the only thing I would advise newcomers is to remain honest. If you don't feel up to a task, there will be people ready to help you through difficult situations. However, it can only happen if one is open and honest about it. Radian colleagues provide a perfect environment to feel comfortable doing so.

	What has been your favorite moment at Radian?

	It has to be when I realized I was a part of building a complete Pricing Process from scratch for a client. It gave me a sense of deeply-rooted satisfaction. It was not until I realized that we achieved the goal that this feeling truly sank in. Not only was I part of the process, I was given a lot of latitude to build it from the ground up.

	 

	To learn more about Radian email me at AAgarwal@radiangroup.com








