Tim Smith
Analyst










Tim Smith
Analyst





	Why did you choose Radian?

	I interned at Radian the summer between my junior and senior year of college and loved the culture of the company. The work that Radian does is very impactful and I wanted a career where I could make a difference. After graduating, Radian was the first company I contacted to start my career.

	What do you most enjoy about what you do?

	I really enjoy being involved in multiple projects at the same time. My workdays are never the same, so I'm constantly being challenged to think and act quickly. Being a part of implementing new programs and tracking their success is also very fulfilling.

	What are your passions outside of work?

	I really enjoy traveling around the world and experiencing new cultures. I also enjoy being active by running, cycling, participating in multiple team sports and getting involved in races.

	What advice would you give new hires?

	My advice to a new hire would be to find an area in the company that you feel needs improvement and spend time outside of the office working on that. Everyone at Radian has a purpose and they all strive to be the best at what they do. 

	What has been your favorite moment at Radian?

	My favorite moment at Radian was when we had a relay race around Lake Calhoun with several people from the office. Chris got everyone involved and it was a really nice way to take a little break that afternoon. Of course, we analyzed the results afterwards—which was almost as fun.

	 

	To learn more about Radian email me at TSmith@radiangroup.com








