	Available Positions at Radian 


		Senior Data Analyst / Consultant - 
		Nashville, TN




	Join Radian’s professional services team to support our business strategy and merchandising analysis projects.  Our goal is to utilize a consumer-focused approach, with sales and merchandising analytics, to identify improvement opportunities for our clients.  You will be part of a team that develops leading edge Retail and Foodservice merchandising analytics utilizing proprietary business planning processes.


	The ideal candidate has strong critical thinking, analytics and database skills with 3 to 7 years of industry experience.  Retail, Manufacturing or CPG experience is preferred.


Primary Responsibilities



	Develop advanced analytics for retail merchandising and foodservice sales planning leveraging client and Radian database extracts
	
Create database tables, relationships and queries to provide foundational analytics structures

	Work with reporting and analytics tools (Excel, Access, Powerpoint, Tableau, etc.)

	Deliver high impact business analytics including:
	

		Define data requirements

		Extract information from client and third-party databases

		Create analytical models for rooutine and ad-hoc analysis



	Develop initiative reporting utilizing test and control, and trend analysis modeling

	Support other strategic client engagements


Capabilities



	Demonstrates critical thinking capabilities

	Possesses strong analytical and problem solving skills

	Strong aptitude with data and information management tools:
	

		MS Excel and Access

		SQL Server

		Corporate data query tools

		Financial or other analytics software



	Strong verbal communication skills

	Ability to work in a fast-paced, collaborative environment with tight deadlines


Experience



	3 to 7 years of professional data and analysis experience (required)

	Finance, business analyst, or logistics planning support role (preferred)


Education



	Bachelors’ degree (required)

	Business, Engineering, or Science major (preferred)


Benefits



	401(k) program with matching

	Health and dental

	Paid vacation and holidays 










		Senior Manager - Perishables / Meat Team - 
		Midwest / East Coast




	Join Radian’s Retail Business Planning (RBP) team to drive our business planning and merchandising analysis projects that are focused on retailers’ Perishables and Meat Departments. We utilize a consumer-focused, fact-based approach with sales and merchandising analytics to define the marketplace opportunities for our clients. You will be based at our client’s office to improve our ability to define and implement leading edge strategies and unique business planning processes for Perishables and Meat departments. We integrate vendor expertise with retailer strategic objectives to maximize the total business potential for all trade partners.

	Radian hires talented, self-starting individuals who have a strong desire to be in the driver’s seat when it comes to their careers. They possess deep analytical skills and prefer a nimble and straightforward working environment where the path is clear for them to make an impact.

	The ideal candidate needs to have Perishables/Meat Department experience in Grocery Retail. Retail analytics or merchandising planning background is required with 5 to 15 years of overall retail, foodservice or food manufacturing experience.

Primary Responsibilites:


Develop consumer-centric insights that lead to innovative programs and initiatives for both the manufacturer and the retailer

Support perishable merchandising business analytics including: data extraction, sales analysis, business insight development, and initiative creation

Lead project tasks in the design of merchandising reporting: business requirements, templates, and initiative evaluation metrics

Develop initiatives and execution improvement recommendations

Support other strategic consulting engagements as necessary


Capabilities


		Demonstrated business acumen

		Able to work with all levels of management

		Possesses strong analytical and problem solving skills

		Has strong written and verbal communication skills

		Excellent experience with software productivity tools, such as:
		

				MS Excel (advanced)

				MS PowerPoint (advanced)

				Data Analysis Skills: Familiarity with corporate sales data and tools



		Ability to work in a fast-paced, team work environment with tight deadlines


Experience


5 to 15 years of overall work experience in retail, foodservice, or consumer packaged goods (required)

3 to 5 years in Perishables / Meat Department retailing (required)

Category management role with a retailer (preferred)

Procurement or financial analysis experience (preferred)


Education


Bachelor’s degree required

Business or Marketing degree preferred 


Benefits


401(k) program with matching

Health and dental insurance

Paid vacation and holidays 









		Supply Chain Planner - 
		Albany, NY & Pittsburgh, PA



Join
Radian’s advanced planning team to support our food industry projects.  You will be part of a client site team at a
major food retailer that develops demand forecasts and procurement plans to
ensure supply alignment in fresh meat. Radian’s team works with the food
processor and the retail client’s leadership teams to align raw material
purchasing, production and distribution to maximize overall sales potential.
	

The
ideal candidate needs to have strong analytical skills with 3 to 5 years of
business analysis experience. The candidate must be able to understand
corporate data hierarchies and produce analytical reports with high data
integrity.  Work experience specifically
in sales forecasting, demand planning or production planning is highly preferred.
Retail, food processor or consumer packaged goods experience is also preferred.  Experience in perishables or meat a plus.


Primary Responsibilites:



	On-site client analyst to support demand planning for consumer ready products 
 

	Deliver specific forecasts:
	

		Aggregated, long-range forecasts for food processor materials planning

		Alignment of individual items to weekly ad planning cycle

		Weekly updates to rolling 6-week planning forecasts
Weekly forecasts for distribution center inbound requirements
Inventory monitoring, forecast vs. actual tracking and purchase order adjustments as required



	Develop ad-hoc reporting to measure forecast alignments

	Define forecasting process improvements across the supply chain

	Support other strategic consulting projects at the client as necessary


Capabilities



	Demonstrated business acumen

	Must be able to work directly with client management teams as a representative of Radian
Possess strong analytical and problem solving skills
Strong written & verbal communication skills

	Excellent experience with software productivity tools:
	

		MS Excel (Advanced)

		MS PowerPoint (Skilled)

		Database Skills: Corporate systems experience, e.g. Microstrategie, Cognos or similiar (Required), MS Access (Preferred)



	Ability to work in a fast-paced, team environment with tight deadlines
Working knowledge of supply chain logistics, demand planning, and analytical forecasting methods



Experience



	3 to 5 years in a supply chain analyst or materials planning role (Required)

	Category management, for demand planning role in Retail, Manufacturing or Consumer Packaged Goods (Preferred)


Education



Bachelor’s degree required

	Finance, Science or Engineering background (preferred)


Benefits



401(k) program

Health and dental insurance

Paid vacation and holidays 

Relocation Assistance 










